snippet.description:
I've had my eye on this lookout tower, or whatever it's called, for the past 103 visits to US-10562.  Getting my wire up there was a dream for so long. On this visit, I asked the Park Rangers if I could have permission to put my paracord over the rail to elevate my Spooltenna radiating element.  They said sure, but be aware of the wasps.  Having some experience with the nasty creatures, I armed myself with a can of spray and scaled the tower.  With the radiating element elevated, I put the feed point on my painter's pole mast up about 18'.  What ensued was an epic Parks on the Air activation.  The DX contacts can in from Puerto Rico, Spain, The Netherlands, France, Croatia, and RUSSIA!  Come along for one of my favorite activations of all time, thanks to Spooltenna.
